Reasoning: The paper deals with the challenges of dealing with large-scale datasets in information retrieval and machine learning, which are topics covered in the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The use of binary codes and hash tables also suggests a connection to Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Data Structures (cs.DS). The proposed multi-index hashing approach and the evaluation of performance on real-world datasets are also relevant to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Databases (cs.DB).
